Sentencas: La-doped titanate materials have been widely investigated as alternative Ni-free anodes for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of La0.4Sr0.6TiO3 synthesized in air for SOFC application

Sentencas: In this study, La0.4Sr0.6TiO3 (LST) was synthesized using the solid-state reaction method and calcined in air.
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of La0.4Sr0.6TiO3 synthesized in air for SOFC application

Sentencas: A three-electrode mode was applied to measure the electrochemical performance of LST-yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) composite anode by testing its impedance spectra and the anode overpotential.
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of La0.4Sr0.6TiO3 synthesized in air for SOFC application

Sentencas: The electrochemical behavior is strongly dependent on the sintering temperature and the YSZ content.
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of La0.4Sr0.6TiO3 synthesized in air for SOFC application

Sentencas: The lowest polarization resistance of 0.26 Omega cm(2) in 97% H-2/3% H2O was obtained on the anode sintered at 1350 degrees C when adding 60 wt% YSZ.
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of La0.4Sr0.6TiO3 synthesized in air for SOFC application

Sentencas: The cell with the LST-YSZ anode was operated at 10,000 ppm H2S-H-2 at 850 degrees C for more than 10 h, and it exhibited excellent sulfur-tolerant ability.
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of La0.4Sr0.6TiO3 synthesized in air for SOFC application

Sentencas: The LST-YSZ anode sintered in air instead of reducing condition is probably a potential anode material for SOFCs.
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of La0.4Sr0.6TiO3 synthesized in air for SOFC application
